    "RESUME": "The aim of TRIFORC is to develop a pipeline for the exploitation of plant triterpenes, one of the largest classes of bioactive plant compounds. They are synthesised by a range of plant families and show an amazing range of structures and biological activities.  Consortium partners will use their know-how and resources to develop the pipeline and produce high-value plant bio-additives for use in new drugs or agrochemicals. Researchers will identify new bioactive compounds from natural resources by investigating biodiversity, including plants that are endangered or difficult to cultivate. Newly discovered triterpenes will be derived through semi-synthesis in plant and microalgal bioreactor-based production systems.  Structure-activity relationships for triterpenoids will be explored using high-throughput screening technology for new chemical compounds with potential agricultural and pharmacological applications. TRIFORC will also develop and increase in scale plant-based bioreactors for commercial production and biorefining of high-value triterpenes.  Bottle necks in triterpene metabolic engineering will be addressed using cutting-edge gene mining. This will be used to create a genetic toolbox and establish a synthetic biology platform for the production of designer triterpenes in organisms suited to bioindustry-scale cultivation.  TRIFORC will therefore guarantee a sustainable supply of high-value plant compounds with new or enhanced biological activities ready for commercialisation.",
